    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nExecuting a external command closes Neovim on the exact moment.\n\nMaybe related with https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/974bc1b0444ba3a235f056ff16e038aaee34863f\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nJust call `:!git --version` for example. The editor closes right away.\n\n<img width=\"1919\" height=\"150\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/69562445-0044-4182-b4d7-e3a5c89ccfe6\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTo show external command output and editor still be open.\nNeovim version `NVIM v0.12.0-dev-2486+g` 2015f19f1b is working as expected:\n\n<img width=\"1919\" height=\"178\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3f9bed3e-a98b-4517-9839-f2bce2aa2a7d\" />\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2610+gc3308fa5fe\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n- Windows 11 Enterprise\n- Linux Mint 22.2 Zara\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n- wezterm 20250212-100137-9da362c7\n- kitty 0.46.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\n- none on Windows\n- xterm-kitty on Linux\n\n### Installation\n\nlatest build on the repository",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-29T04:58:34Z",
